article.headline: Norfolk State 68, Morgan State 65
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Ryan Grier scored six points during a game-ending 9-2 run Saturday that lifted Norfolk State to a 68-65 victory against Morgan State. The Spartans (6-12, 5-4 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) trailed 63-59 after Ronald Timus' dunk for the Bears with 2:14 to play, but sandwiched a 3-pointer Grier and two free throws by Chakowby Hicks around another dunk by Timus with 1:28 to play. Grier then hit two free throws with six seconds left to give the Spartans the lead, and he and Hicks each hit one more free throw in the closing seconds to end it. Grier, Hicks and Nicholas Byrd all had 13 points for the Spartans. Timus and Reggie Winkfield scored 19 apiece to led the Bears.
